      <p>Jeremy Tribby is an artist, designer, and programmer from California. He is the creator of the Arthouse family of typefaces for NBC, as well as the open source Google Font, Barlow. Currently, he works as a design technologist at <a href="https://plaid.com/">Plaid</a>. In the past he worked as an engineer at the Electronic Frontier Foundation (EFF), the civil liberties non-profit, and in various roles at a number of startups. Jeremy studied art and art history at UC Berkeley.<p>
